HEADWORD: Indoaniline
<hw>In`do*an"i*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ind</ets>igo + <ets>aniline</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Any one of a series of artificial blue dyes, in appearance
resembling indigo, for which they are often used as
substitutes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

